					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I like the debugging features, but found a little weird that the graphics in the VRAM viewer stretch with the window, and there's no way to snap to an integer scale, so everything is always distorted. I liked the &quot;assumed palette&quot; feature, but it would be nice if we could manually pick palettes too. Also, the BG Map and the tile info graphics are drawn with patterns that are mapped at the end of the frame, which doesn't allow us to debug the upper parts of the screen when patterns are switched mid screen. FCEUX has a &quot;show on scanline&quot; box so that you can sample the PPU on specific scanlines.</div>

